Web Infrastructure Design

Load Balancer (HAProxy Cluster):

Two HAProxy Load Balancers configured as a cluster for high availability and load distribution.
Responsible for routing incoming traffic to the appropriate servers based on load balancing rules.

Web Server:

One dedicated server for hosting static content, such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and media files.
Nginx or Apache can be used as the web server software.
Configured to handle web requests, serve static files, and cache content for improved performance.

Application Server:

One dedicated server for hosting the application logic and processing dynamic content.
Node.js, Django, Ruby on Rails, or any other application framework can be used.
Configured to handle application-specific logic, process user requests, and interact with the database.

Database Server:

One dedicated server for hosting the database management system (e.g., MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB).
Responsible for storing and managing application data.
Regular backups, security configurations, and redundancy measures should be implemented to ensure data integrity and availability.
